   view="""{{{ [<item>get[caption]else<item>] }}}""" colors="yes" listsize="10" focusPopup="yes" cancelPopups="no"
   filter="[tag[background]] [enlist{TiddlyTools/Settings/Colors/X11Names}]" placeholder=" " tooltip="""$tip$""" />
</$set>
\end

\define slidebar-in()   cubic-bezier(0.165, 0.84, 0.44, 1)
\define slidebar-out()  ease-out

<pre>
/* SLIDEBAR */
.<<barclass>>
   { position:fixed; z-index:999;
     top:<<bartop>>; left:<<barleft>>; bottom:<<barbottom>>; right:<<barright>>;
     width:<<barwidth>>; min-width:<<barmin>>; max-width:<<barmax>>; height:<<barheight>>; }

/* TRAY */
.<<barclass>> .tt-slidebar-tray
   { position:absolute;
     top:<<traytop>>; left:<<trayleft>>; bottom:<<traybottom>>; right:<<trayright>>;
     height:<<trayheight>>; width:<<traywidth>>; min-width:<<traymin>>; max-width:<<traymax>>;
     margin-left:<<traymargin>>; margin-right:<<traymargin>>; <<trayhide>> }

/* PANEL */
.<<barclass>> .tt-slidebar-panel
   { <<panelstyle>>; }

/* PIN BUTTON */
.<<barclass>> .tt-slidebar-button
   { z-index:-1; height:100%; width:100%;
     opacity:0.3; color:<<buttoncolor>>; background:<<buttonbg>>;
     white-space:nowrap; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold;
   }
.<<barclass>> .tt-slidebar-button:hover
   { opacity:0.6; }

/* SHADOWBOX STYLES */
.<<barclass>> .tt-shadowbox:not(.inset)
   { font-size:calc(<<barfontsize>>); background:<<barbg>>; width:<<traywidth>>; }

/* DEBUG: SHOW HOVER ZONES */
/* <$checkbox tiddler="$:/temp/slidebars/debug/showzones" field="text" checked="yes" unchecked="no" default="no">show hover zones</$checkbox> */
<$reveal state="$:/temp/slidebars/debug/showzones" type="match" text="yes">
   .<<barclass>>                         { background:rgba(127,127,255,0.2); }
   .<<barclass>>       .tt-slidebar-tray { background:rgba(127,255,127,0.2); }
   .<<barclass>>:hover                   { background:rgba(255,127,127,0.2); }
</$reveal>

<$reveal state=<<barstay>> type="nomatch" text="no">
   /* STICKY (STAY) PANEL STYLES - ALWAYS SHOW, BRING TO FRONT ON HOVER */
   .<<barclass>>                     { z-index:<<barz>>; } /* -1=BEHIND TIDDLERS, 999=ON TOP */
   .<<barclass>>:hover               { z-index:<<barzhover>>; }
   .<<barclass>> .tt-slidebar-tray   { <<trayshow>> }
   .<<barclass>> .tt-slidebar-button { opacity:1;   }
</$reveal>

<$reveal state=<<barstay>> type="nomatch" text="yes">
   /* SLIDEOUT (AUTO-HIDE) PANEL STYLES */
   .<<barclass>>                         { z-index:<<barzhover>>; } /* ALWAYS ON TOP */
   .<<barclass>>:hover                   { z-index:<<barzhover>>; }
   .<<barclass>>       .tt-slidebar-tray { <<trayhide>> }
   <$reveal state=<<barhover>> type="nomatch" text="no">
      /* HOVER - SHOW ON MOUSEOVER */
      .<<barclass>>:hover .tt-slidebar-tray { <<trayshow>> }
      /* DEBUG: ENABLE/DISABLE TRANSITIONS */
      /* <$checkbox tiddler="$:/temp/slidebars/debug/transitions" field="text" checked="no" unchecked="yes" default="yes">disable transitions</$checkbox> */
      <$reveal state="$:/temp/slidebars/debug/transitions" type="nomatch" text="no">
         /* TRANSITIONS */
         /* slidebar-in  = ease-in */
         /* slidebar-out = cubic-bezier(0.165, 0.84, 0.44, 1) http://easings.net/#easeOutQuart */
         .<<barclass>>                         { transition: z-index 0s 1s, width 0s 1s; }
         .<<barclass>>:hover                   { transition: z-index 0s 0s, width 0s 0s; }
         @media (pointer:coarse) { /* "FAT FINGER" TOUCH SCREENS (SLIDE-IN, POP-OUT) */
            .<<barclass>>       .tt-slidebar-tray { transition: margin 0s 0s   <<slidebar-out>>, opacity 0s 0s;   }
            .<<barclass>>:hover .tt-slidebar-tray { transition: margin 1s 0.5s <<slidebar-in>>,  opacity 1s 0.5s; }
         }
         @media (pointer:fine) { /* DESKTOP/MOUSE (SLIDE-IN, SLIDE-OUT) */
            .<<barclass>>       .tt-slidebar-tray { transition: margin 1s 0s   <<slidebar-out>>, opacity 2s 0s;   }
            .<<barclass>>:hover .tt-slidebar-tray { transition: margin 1s 0.5s <<slidebar-in>>,  opacity 1s 0.5s; }
         }
      </$reveal>
   </$reveal>
</$reveal>
</pre>

\define debug(msg)
<$action-setfield $tiddler="$:/temp/notify" text="""swapping $(source_label)$ and $(target_label)$ panels"""/>
<$action-sendmessage $message="tm-notify" $param="$:/temp/notify"/>
\end

\define barDrop()
<$vars action={{$:/dragdata!!action}} droptag={{$:/dragdata!!bartag}} >
<$reveal text=<<action>> type="match" default="bardrag">
   <$reveal text=<<droptag>> type="nomatch" default=<<bartag>>>
      <$set name="source_panels"  filter="[tag<droptag>!has[draft.of]]">
      <$set name="source_barname" filter="[title<droptag>removeprefix[$:/tags/]removesuffix[SlideBar]addsuffix[Bar/Label]]">
      <$set name="source_label"   filter="[title[$:/config/TiddlyTools]getindex<source_barname>]">
      <$set name="target_panels"  filter="[tag<bartag>!has[draft.of]]">
      <$set name="target_barname" filter="[title<bartag>removeprefix[$:/tags/]removesuffix[SlideBar]addsuffix[Bar/Label]]">
      <$set name="target_label"   filter="[title[$:/config/TiddlyTools]getindex<target_barname>]">
         <$list filter=<<source_panels>> variable="panelID"> <$action-setfield $tiddler=<<panelID>> tags=<<bartag>>  $timestamp="no" /> </$list>
         <$list filter=<<target_panels>> variable="panelID"> <$action-setfield $tiddler=<<panelID>> tags=<<droptag>> $timestamp="no" /> </$list>
         <$action-setfield $tiddler="$:/config/TiddlyTools" $index=<<target_barname>> $value=<<source_label>> />
         <$action-setfield $tiddler="$:/config/TiddlyTools" $index=<<source_barname>> $value=<<target_label>> />
         <<debug>>
      </$set></$set></$set></$set></$set></$set>
   </$reveal>
</$reveal>
</$vars>
<$action-deletetiddler $filter="[prefix[$:/dragdata]]"/>
\end

<!-- SHOW THE SLIDEBAR TRAY CONTAINING TAGGED CONTENT WITH PIN/UNPIN BUTTON -->
<$list filter="[tag<bartag>!has[draft.of]limit[1]]" variable="has-items">
<div class=<<barclass>>>
   <$draggable tag="span" tiddler="bardrag"
      startactions="""<$action-setfield $tiddler="$:/dragdata" action="bardrag" bartag=<<bartag>> />"""
        endactions="""<$action-deletetiddler $filter="[prefix[$:/dragdata]]"/>""" >
   <$droppable actions=<<barDrop>>>
   <$reveal state=<<barstay>> type="match" text="no">
      <$button class="tc-btn-invisible tt-slidebar-button"
         tooltip="pin slidebar (keep visible)">
         <<barpin>>
         <$action-setfield $tiddler=<<config>> $index=<<barname>> $value="yes"/>
      </$button>
   </$reveal>
   <$reveal state=<<barstay>> type="nomatch" text="no">
      <$button class="tc-btn-invisible tt-slidebar-button"
         tooltip="unpin slidebar (auto show/hide)">
         <<barunpin>>
         <$action-setfield $tiddler=<<config>> $index=<<barname>> $value="no"/>
      </$button>
   </$reveal>
   </$droppable>
   </$draggable>
   <div class="tt-slidebar-tray">
      <div class="tt-slidebar-panel">
         <$list filter="[tag<bartag>!has[draft.of]]"><$transclude/></$list>
      </div>
   </div>
</div>
</$list>

\define toc-config()         $:/config/TiddlyTools/TOC
\define toc-template()       TiddlyTools/TOC/Template
\define toc-ignore-tags()    bookcover Chapter

\define toc-open-all()       $(toc-config)$##OpenAll
\define toc-branch-is-open() $(toc-config)$##$(path)$/$(item)$
\define toc-item-is-branch() [tag[$(item)$]] $(excluded)$ -[[$(item)$]] +[limit[1]]

\define toc-show-branch()    <$macrocall $name="toc-tree" here=<<item>> max=<<max>> exclude=<<excluded>> path=<<path>> level={{{ [<level>add[1]] }}}/>

\define toc-show-item()
<span class="readertools">
   {{$(item)$||$(toc-template)$}}
</span>
<span class="authortools">
   <$droppable actions=<<toc-item-drop>>>
      <div class="tc-droppable-placeholder tt-toc-placeholder"></div> 
      <$draggable tiddler=<<item>> startactions=<<toc-item-dragstart>> endactions=<<toc-item-dragend>> dragimagetype="blank">
         <div title="drag to rearrange items">
            {{$(item)$||$(toc-template)$}}
         </div>
      </$draggable>
      <div class="tc-droppable-placeholder tt-toc-placeholder"><<toc-item-dragtip>></div> 
   </$droppable>
</span>
\end

\define toc-item-dragdata()    $:/temp/TOC/dragdata
\define toc-item-dragstart()   <$action-setfield      $tiddler=<<toc-item-dragdata>> text=<<actionTiddler>> />
\define toc-item-dragend()     <$action-deletetiddler $tiddler=<<toc-item-dragdata>> />

\define toc-item-dragtip()
<$vars actionTiddler={{{ [<toc-item-dragdata>get[text]] }}}>
<$list filter="[<actionTiddler>!match<item>]"> <!-- DON'T SHOW TIP ON SELF -->
   <div class="tt-toc-dragtip">
      <nobr>drop <$tiddler tiddler=<<actionTiddler>>>''<<toc-caption>>''</$tiddler></nobr><br>
      <nobr>onto <$tiddler tiddler=<<item>>         >''<<toc-caption>>''</$tiddler></nobr><br>
      <div style="font-size:80%; border-top:1px solid; margin-top:0.2em;">
         NO KEY=insert before, SHIFT=insert after, CTRL=drop into
      </div>
   </div>
</$list>
</$vars>
\end

\define toc-item-drop()
<$reveal default=<<actionTiddler>> type="nomatch" text=<<item>>> <!-- DON'T DROP ON SELF -->
   <!-- get OLDTAG and NEWTAG, exclude special TiddlyBook tags -->
   <$vars sourcetags={{{ [<actionTiddler>get[tags]] }}}
          targettags={{{ [<item>get[tags]] }}}>
   <$vars oldtag={{{ [enlist<sourcetags>!enlist<toc-ignore-tags>] }}}
          newtag={{{ [enlist<targettags>!enlist<toc-ignore-tags>] }}}>
   <$list filter="[<modifier>match[normal]]"><!-- DROP BEFORE SIBLING -->
      <$macrocall $name="toc-item-drop-action" oldtag=<<oldtag>> newtag=<<newtag>> filter="+[putbefore<item>]" />
   </$list>
   <$list filter="[<modifier>match[shift]]"><!-- DROP AFTER SIBLING -->
      <$macrocall $name="toc-item-drop-action" oldtag=<<oldtag>> newtag=<<newtag>> filter="+[putafter<item>]" />
   </$list>
   <$list filter="[<modifier>match[ctrl]]"><!-- DROP AS CHILD -->
      <$macrocall $name="toc-item-drop-action" oldtag=<<oldtag>> newtag=<<item>> filter="" />
   </$list>
   </$vars>
   </$vars>
</$reveal>
\end

\define toc-item-drop-action(oldtag,newtag,filter)
<$set name="order" filter="[title[$newtag$]tagging[]]">
<$list filter=<<order>>> <$action-deletefield $field="list-before"/> <$action-deletefield $field="list-after"/> </$list>
<$action-listops $tiddler=<<actionTiddler>> $field="tags" $subfilter="-[title[$oldtag$]] [title[$newtag$]]" />
<$action-listops $tiddler="$oldtag$"        $field="list" $subfilter="-[<actionTiddler>]" />
<$action-listops $tiddler="$newtag$"        $field="list" $subfilter="[enlist<order>] -[<actionTiddler>] [<actionTiddler>] $filter$" />
</$set>
\end

\define toc-list(here,max,exclude,level:"1")
<!-- SHOW ALL TOC TIDDLER TITLES AS A FLAT LIST (SIMPLE RECURSION) -->
<$list filter="""[tag[$here$]] $exclude$ -[[$here$]]""">
   <$text text="[["/><<currentTiddler>><$text text="]]"/><br>
   <$reveal default="$level$" type="nomatch" text="$max$">
      <$macrocall $name="toc-list" here=<<currentTiddler>> max="$max$" exclude="""$exclude$ -[[$here$]]""" level={{{ [[$level$]add[1]] }}}/>
   </$reveal>
</$list>
\end

\define toc-all(here,max,exclude,path,level:"1")
<!-- SHOW ENTIRE TREE FULLY EXPANDED (SIMPLE RECURSION) -->
<span class="tt-toc-all">
<$list filter="""[tag[$here$]] $exclude$ -[[$here$]]""">
   <$vars item=<<currentTiddler>> max="$max$" excluded="""$exclude$ -[[$here$]]""" path="""$path$/$here$""" level="$level$" >
   <<toc-show-item>>
   <$reveal default=<<level>> type="nomatch" text=<<max>>>
      <div class="tt-toc-indent">
          <$macrocall $name="toc-all" here=<<item>> max=<<max>> exclude=<<excluded>> path=<<path>> level={{{ [<level>add[1]] }}} />
      </div>
   </$reveal>
   </$vars>
</$list>
</span>
\end

\define toc-tree(here,max,exclude,path,level:"1")
<!-- EXPANDABLE TREE WITH OPEN/CLOSE ALL, OPEN/CLOSE BRANCH, AUTO-OPEN CURRENT BRANCH -->
<span class="tt-toc-tree">
<$list filter="""[tag[$here$]] $exclude$ -[[$here$]]""">
   <$vars item=<<currentTiddler>> max="$max$" excluded="""$exclude$ -[[$here$]]""" path="""$path$/$here$""" level="$level$" >
   <<toc-show-item>>
   <div class="tt-toc-indent">
      <$reveal state=<<toc-open-all>> type="match" text="yes">
         <$reveal default=<<level>> type="nomatch" text=<<max>>>
            <<toc-show-branch>>
         </$reveal>
      </$reveal>
      <$reveal state=<<toc-open-all>> type="nomatch" text="yes">
         <$reveal state=<<toc-branch-is-open>> type="match" text="open">
            <$reveal default=<<level>> type="nomatch" text=<<max>>>
               <<toc-show-branch>>
            </$reveal>
         </$reveal>
         <$reveal state=<<toc-branch-is-open>> type="nomatch" text="open">
            <$macrocall $name="toc-show-if-parent" here={{$:/HistoryList!!current-tiddler}}/>
         </$reveal>
      </$reveal>
   </div>
   </$vars>
</$list>
</span>
\end

\define toc-show-if-parent(here,exclude)
<!-- SHOW BRANCH ONLY IF IT CONTAINS CURRENT TIDDLER -->
<$reveal text="""$here$""" type="match" default=<<item>>>
   <<toc-show-branch>>
</$reveal>
<$reveal text="""$here$""" type="nomatch" default=<<item>>>
   <$list filter="""[title[$here$]tags[]] $exclude$ -[[$here$]]""">
      <$macrocall $name="toc-show-if-parent" here=<<currentTiddler>> exclude="""$exclude$ -[[$here$]]"""/>
   </$list>
</$reveal>
\end

\define toc-toggle-branch()
<!-- OPEN/CLOSE ONE BRANCH -->
<span class="tt-toc-toggle">
<$list filter=<<toc-item-is-branch>> emptyMessage="&emsp;">
   <$reveal state=<<toc-branch-is-open>> type="match" text="open">
       <$button class="tc-btn-invisible" tooltip="collapse this item">
         <$action-setfield    $tiddler=<<toc-config>> $index="""$(path)$/$(item)$"""/> <!-- DELETEINDEX -->
         {{$:/core/images/down-arrow}}
      </$button>
   </$reveal>
   <$reveal state=<<toc-branch-is-open>> type="nomatch" text="open">
      <$button class="tc-btn-invisible" tooltip="expand this item">
         <$action-setfield $tiddler=<<toc-config>> $index="""$(path)$/$(item)$""" $value="open"/>
         {{$:/core/images/right-arrow}}
      </$button>
  </$reveal>
</$list>
</span>
\end

\define toc-toggle-all(class:"tc-button")
<!-- OPEN/CLOSE ALL BRANCHES (OVERIDES INDIVIDUAL TOGGLES) -->
<span class="tt-toc-toggleall">
<$reveal state=<<toc-open-all>> type="match" text="yes">
   <$button class="""$class$""" tooltip="collapse all items">
      <$action-setfield $tiddler=<<toc-config>> $index="OpenAll" $value="no"/>
      {{$:/core/images/chevron-up}}
   </$button>
</$reveal>
<$reveal state=<<toc-open-all>> type="nomatch" text="yes">
   <$button class="""$class$""" tooltip="expand all items">
      <$action-setfield $tiddler=<<toc-config>> $index="OpenAll" $value="yes"/>
      {{$:/core/images/chevron-down}}
   </$button>
</$reveal>
</span>
\end






/*\
title: TiddlyTools/TOC/scrollhere.js
type: application/javascript
module-type: widget
author: Eric Shulman

Widget to force a parent element to scroll into view.
Usage: <$scrollhere/>

\*/
(function(){

/*jslint node: true, browser: true */
/*global $tw: false */
"use strict";

var Widget = require("$:/core/modules/widgets/widget.js").widget;
var ScrollHereWidget = function(parseTreeNode,options) {
	this.initialise(parseTreeNode,options);
};
ScrollHereWidget.prototype = new Widget();
ScrollHereWidget.prototype.render = function(parent,nextSibling) {
	if (parent.scrollIntoViewIfNeeded)
		return parent.scrollIntoViewIfNeeded(false);
	if (parent.scrollIntoView)
		return parent.scrollIntoView(false);
};
ScrollHereWidget.prototype.refresh = function(changedTiddlers) {
	return true;
};
exports.scrollhere = ScrollHereWidget;
})();

@@float:right;text-align:right;[img width=300 [images/twcomsnap.png]]@@The standard ~TiddlyWiki page layout is divided into two parts.
<<showLinks "" "floatleft tt-shadowbox" style:"margin:0.5em">>

The left side of the page is called the [[Story River|TheStoryRiver]], and is used to display a column of [[Tiddler Viewer|TheTiddlerViewer]] panels.

The right side of the page is called the [[Sidebar|TheSidebar]], and provides access to the [[Control Panel|TheControlPanel]] for managing the configuration of your ~TiddlyWiki.

It also provides a [[Search|TheSearchTool]] mechanism for quickly finding tiddlers by matching titles, text, or tags.

In addition, the [[Sidebar Lists|TheSidebarLists]] show a set of tabs that organize your tiddlers based on different categories, such as "Open Tiddlers", "Recent Changes" (sorted by modification date), "All Tiddlers" (sorted by name), etc.  These tabs make it easy to manually navigate directly to the tiddlers you want.






* Simple Transclusion
** "translation" + "inclusion"
** allows embedding of information and formatting stored in different tiddlers
*** ``{{TiddlerName}}``
*** ``{{TiddlerName!!fieldname}}`` or ``{{TiddlerName##indexname}}``
*** ``{{!!fieldname}}``
* Transclusion as a "template"
** enables display of information stored in the current tiddler, using formatting provided in a separate "template" tiddler

   <br>
   @@.changelog.smaller <$transclude tiddler=<<changeLog>> mode="block" />@@
</div>
</$vars>
\end

''So, is ~TiddlyWiki a document, a website, or an application?''  All three, depending on who you are and what you use it for.

!!Own it like a document...

Most people who use computers are already familiar with several ''common document types'' such as text files, word processing, spreadsheets, images, sounds, video, etc., each with their own internal structure: text files are a simple "stream of characters", word processing embodies "pages" of formatted content with headers, footers, margins, etc., spreadsheets provide grids with formulae, variables, and graphs, and media files contain compressed binary data in a variety of media-specific formats.

For each of these document types, you ''don't need to worry about how the contents are stored''.  As long as you have a compatible application installed on your system (e.g, Word, Excel, ~MediaPlayer, etc.) you can view or make changes to those documents.

In many ways, a ''~TiddlyWiki is just another type of document'' that happens to offer the familiar ''"links and forms"'' //hypertext// interface that is used throughout the web.  However, unlike other document types, which separate the data and the program, each ~TiddlyWiki file contains a complete copy of its internal "core" code, ''combining both application and data'' into a single file.

!!...Use it like a website

Because ~TiddlyWiki content uses links and forms, it seems to ''work like a website''.  As you click on links, additional "pages" of content appear, and there are places to type, buttons to press, lists and checkboxes to select, etc.  However, unlike most websites, ~TiddlyWiki does not require a remote server or even a network connection to access information.

Instead, ~TiddlyWiki works like any other document on your computer: it is ''stored locally as a single file'' that is read and displayed by a separate program (in this case, your favorite web browser).  Nearly all modern computers come with at least one web browser application pre-installed, so there is ''virtually __nothing__ to install'' to use a ~TiddlyWiki file.

In addition, because each ~TiddlyWiki document contains a complete copy of its core code, it is ''extremely portable'', and can run on virtually any system.  This makes it ''easy to share your information'' and collaborate with others simply by giving them a copy of your ~TiddlyWiki file for them to view, edit, and send back for inclusion in your original file.

Because each ~TiddlyWiki is a separate HTML file, you can simply copy it onto a USB "flash drive", send it as an email attachment, post it on a shared local fileserver for others to download, or even upload it and host it on a general purpose web server for remote public viewing.

!!Self-contained custom applications

You can also think of ~TiddlyWiki as an ''application framework'' that provides its own programmable environment that allows you to ''customize the functionality'' for loading, editing, displaying, and saving changes to your files.  Nearly every aspect of ~TiddlyWiki's interface has been built using ~TiddlyWiki itself.  This makes it possible to modify its default appearance and behaviors to ''create unique custom-built experiences''.

~TiddlyWiki has a rich set of built-in features that let you manage and present your information in a variety of ways.  In addition to ''basic formatting'' syntax (e.g., bold/italic, paragraph breaks, indentation, bullet lists, tables, embedded images, etc.), ~TiddlyWiki provides an advanced "filter" mechanism that lets you ''group information based on specific criteria'', and then summarize and format the results to suit your particular needs.  ~TiddlyWiki also offers the power of "transclusions" and "macros" - features that let you ''easily re-use and re-combine your information'' for different purposes at different times.

There is also a sophisticated "plugin" system that permits you to ''extend ~TiddlyWiki's capabilities'' by downloading and adding extra programming that operates as an overlay to the core system.  This can include features and functions that allow you to manipulate and display information in new ways and/or produce new output formats.  Plugins are ''easily published and shared'' with others, allowing them to add the same extensions to their own ~TiddlyWiki documents as well.

Combined, these abilities allow ~TiddlyWiki to be used to construct and deliver ''highly interactive custom applications'' that can be used to gather, analyze, present and summarize information to more effectively achieve your goals.






@@float:right;<a href="http://www.tiddlywinks.org/" target="_blank">[img width="150px" [images/tiddlywinks.png]]</a>@@
@@font-size:150%;''"~TiddlyWiki"''@@... Let's be honest, when you first hear the name, you might laugh a little, and then perhaps think of the children's game, <a href="http://www.tiddlywinks.org/" target="_blank">~TiddlyWinks</a>.  You might also wonder if an application with such a silly name could really be used for serious work.

Despite the name, @@font-size:150%;''~TiddlyWiki is not a toy.''@@  It is actually a very powerful tool that can help you create and manage lots of different kinds of information that you use in your daily life.

Of course, when it first started, the word "Google" was also simply a silly-sounding name -- an [[accidental misspelling of the mathematical term, "googol"|http://graphics.stanford.edu/~dk/google_name_origin.html]].  Now, Google's services are used //hundreds of millions// of times a day by people throughout the world, and [["Google" is listed as a verb in the Oxford English Dictionary|http://www.oxforddictionaries.com/us/definition/american_english/google]]!

As William Shakespeare wrote in Romeo and Juliet, "[[What's in a name?|http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A_rose_by_any_other_name_would_smell_as_sweet]]". In the case of ~TiddlyWiki, its name is composed of two terms that represent some of its most important traits:

@@float:left;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Three-spined_stickleback" target="_blank">[img width="230px" [images/stickleback.png]]</a>@@
''//"Tiddly"// is a British slang term that means //"something small".//''  Other familiar variations on the word include "tiddler" (a small bait fish, the [[Three-Spined Stickleback|http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Three-spined_stickleback]], found in ponds and streams), and "toddler" (a small child).

@@font-size:150%;''~TiddlyWiki is small.''@@
With a core system that weighs in at a little over //two megabytes//, it is just a mere fraction of the size of most other applications today, which often use up many //hundreds of megabytes// or even //several gigabytes// when installed on your system. 

@@float:right;<a href="http://c2.com/doc/etymology.html" target="_blank">[img width="200px" [images/wiki-bus.jpg]]</a>@@
In the Hawaiian language, ''//"Wiki"// means quick, and //"wiki wiki"// means //"very quick"//''.   At the Honolulu International Airport, the Wiki Wiki Shuttle is a fare-free shuttle bus system, carrying people and baggage between the various terminals.

@@font-size:150%;''~TiddlyWiki is quick.''@@
It allows you to enter your information without a lot of planning and setup, it's relatively easy to learn and easy to use, and there is almost no installation required, so you can get started right away!

So, as [[The Bard of Avon|https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William_Shakespeare]] might have said: @@font-size:150%;''a ~TiddlyWiki by any other name would still be //small// and //quick//.''@@
